name: Pharmacy_Billing_Management_System_Web_Application
description: A comprehensive Java-based web application designed to streamline billing and inventory management for pharmaceutical stores. The system features secure user authentication, employee and inventory management, automated invoice generation, and sales analytics. Built using Java, Struts 2, MySQL, and JSP, it offers an intuitive interface and backend.

name: RAG-Driven-Knowledge-Extraction-Using-Llama-3.1-NVIDIA-NIM-and-Neo4j
description: This project leverages the power of Llama 3.1's native function-calling capabilities, NVIDIA NIM microservices, and the Neo4j graph database to retrieve structured data from the FDA Adverse Event Reporting System (FAERS).

name: Retail-Operations-Hub
description: This project aims to create an e-commerce platform using a microservices architecture. The platform will consist of three main microservices: Product Service, Order Service, and Inventory Service. Each service will handle specific business functionalities, ensuring a modular, scalable, and maintainable system.
